# Narration Plan — {{ project_name }}

The single source of truth for narration audio this project generates
with the `generate-audio` skill. Narration text lives **inline** in
your source markdown as `> 🎙️` blockquotes — this file just records
the project-level voice/model defaults and acts as the review surface.

**Voice:** rachel
**Model:** eleven_multilingual_v2

> The generator scans configured source files (`module-*.md` by default)
> for contiguous blockquoted lines that begin with `> 🎙️ `. Each block
> becomes one MP3 in `audio/<source-stem>/NN_<slug>.mp3` plus a
> `manifest.json` recording the stripped text sent to ElevenLabs.
>
> Override the project voice or model with `--voice <name-or-id>` or
> `--model <id>`. CLI flags always win over plan frontmatter. Plan
> frontmatter wins over kit defaults.
>
> Cost: ElevenLabs `eleven_multilingual_v2` is **1 credit per character**.
> The end-of-run summary prints chars-sent = credits-spent so you can
> pace work against your monthly cap.

